== English ==
=== Verb ===
'''[[run]] [[a]] [[mile]]'''
# {{idiom}} (''predominantly UK'') To [[escape]], [[flee]] or [[leave]] a [[situation]] or [[relationship]], usually as a result of a [[shock]]ing or sudden [[announcement]] or [[revelation]].
#: Person A: ''If I told him that I had kids, he'd '''run a mile'''.''
#: Person B: ''So what are you going to do? Wait till you get married?!?''